This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with building an Offensive Language Classifier using different architectures and algorithms. Additionally, the paper discusses pre-processing strategies and evaluates the classifiers on a test set. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves building classifiers using deep learning methods. 

cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with identifying offensive language on social media platforms. 

Finally, cs.CY (Computers and Society) could also be a possible sub-category as the paper deals with identifying and categorizing offensive language, which has societal implications.
